    "instruction": "For confirmation, extract a compact per-KPI anomaly summary for cmdb_id == 'adservice' using the previously computed global P95 values and the observed window 2022-03-21 01:30:00+08 through 2022-03-21 01:59:00+08. Return at most 20 rows sorted by relative breach (treat p95==0 with max_value>0 as largest) then anomaly_count desc. For each KPI row include: kpi_name, anomaly_count, earliest_anomaly_ts, max_value_in_window, global_p95, abs_breach = max_value_in_window - global_p95, and rel_breach (if global_p95==0 and max_value_in_window>0 set rel_breach to '>>1e6 (p95=0 & value>0)', else numeric). Also, check error_logs (df_error) for any rows with cmdb_id == 'adservice' in the same observed window and return a small dict: error_rows_count and earliest_error_ts (or None). Return only these compact results (no full raw series)."
